<subSubSection id="193879D10818AEDDE57BEF76C2A09652" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="ECD97BBCBE57C10BC0A6A0BD20A0D0EF" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<pageBreakToken id="625F07E8A4537DC31BB6EDAB838BCCEB" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" start="start">Diagnosis</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E6BBEF5298D76D6F3FCFB17ACA1BE879" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Differs from the typical variety by the capitula 2-3 mm in diameter, flowers 5-10 per capitulum, the pistillate flowers with sepals elliptic, uniformly thickened in fruit and dispersed with the fruit; petals of pistillate flowers oblong to oblong-spatulate with broadly rounded to truncate apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
